  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Conceptualizing Companion Couture**\n\nI\'m focusing on \"Companion Couture,\" a luxury companion placement website concept. The goal is to emulate Dior.com\'s emotional and editorial design language. I\'m exploring how to translate this luxury aesthetic to the specific needs of affluent families and professionals seeking companions.\n\n\n**Refining Brand Identity**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the visual style and site structure for \"Companion Couture.\" I\'ve specified a minimalist luxury aesthetic with large cinematic photography, editorial layouts, and champagne gold accents. The typography will be elegant serif, and I want to use lifestyle imagery to convey a sense of exclusivity. The site will feature sections like \"Available Companions,\" \"The Companion Couture Experience,\" and a beautifully styled interactive application form. The tone will be warm, sophisticated, trustworthy, exclusive, and emotional. I aim to prioritize storytelling and emotional connection above direct sales. Subtle micro-animations will be used for interactive elements.\n\n\n**Evaluating Tech Stack**\n\nI\'m evaluating the technical underpinnings of this project. It appears to be a client-side Vite React application with a strong emphasis on visual presentation and user interaction. The packages installed, like `@google/genai` and `motion`, suggest potential for image generation and dynamic UI elements. I\'m noting the absence of a custom server, implying a focus on client-side functionality and data fetching.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will read the instructions in the `image-generation` skill to see how to generate and use luxury-themed canine and lifestyle images for our editorial Companion Couture website."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 225813705
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
