  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Generating Key Visuals**\n\nI\'m now focused on using the `generate_image` tool. I aim to create several high-quality visuals: a hero banner, companion shots, and images that reflect a luxury lifestyle. The goal is up to 5 diverse image assets that are highly detailed and capture the essence of the application\'s aesthetic. I\'ll focus on delivering a great first impression.\n\n\n**Refining Initial Concepts**\n\nI\'ve decided to name the application \"Companion Couture\" and updated `metadata.json` with a detailed description aligning with a luxury, editorial aesthetic, akin to Dior.com. I\'ve also identified a need to import specific fonts like \"Playfair Display\" or \"Cormorant Garamond\" for headings, aiming for that ultra-luxury, editorial feel. These fonts will be defined in `src/index.css`.\n\n\n**Defining Font Pairing**\n\nI\'ve finalized the font pairing for \"Companion Couture.\" I\'ll be using \"Cormorant Garamond\" for headings to achieve an elegant, luxury-fashion editorial look, paired with \"Inter\" for a clean, modern UI feel. For specifications and important numbers, I\'ll incorporate \"JetBrains Mono\" to add a bespoke, authenticated element. I\'m focusing on defining this in `src/index.css`.\n\n\n**Producing Image Assets**\n\nI\'m now generating image assets. I\'m focusing on four key visuals: a portrait of a Maltese or Cavapoo puppy with luxury clothing, a Golden Retriever puppy in a garden, a Toy Poodle with designer luggage, and a luxury living room scene with a dog. I will aim for a photorealistic and editorial style in 3:4 or 16:9 aspect ratios, depending on the image. I am leveraging the `generate_image` tool, using excellent prompts to realize these visuals. I can run these in parallel or series.\n\n\n"
