    thinking: "**Defining App Structure**\n\nI\'m now focusing on defining the `App.tsx` structure, specifically the main view. I\'m breaking down its sections, initially identifying the essential components: the `Header`, which will be linked to `activeTab` and `setActiveTab`, and then the individual \"Pages\" section.\n\n\n**Developing Home Screen Content**\n\nI\'m now diving into the `home` view, starting with a striking hero section. I\'m visualizing a full-screen cinematic experience with minimalist design. I am going to include text and a button, linked to the `companions` section. Following this will be a preview of \"Our Heritage,\" and a slider showcasing available companions. I\'m also considering a feature block highlighting our savoir-faire, and Journal highlights. Lastly, an elegant CTA banner to round it all out.\n\n\n**Curating Summer Placements**\n\nI am now structuring the summer 2026 placement view. I\'m building out the available placements component with filter options for gender, breed, and status. I\'m focusing on a visually appealing grid display, incorporating animations and hover effects. The design will show detailed dog information, including registry, coat, size, and birthdate, linked to a modal for further details. I am also planning on including Experience and About sections.\n\n\n**Structuring Appointment Types**\n\nI\'m now integrating the appointment booking functionality. I am thinking through the components for the `journal`, including an editorial grid and beautiful entry display, either as an overlay or inline. The `application` component is next, which will involve the `<ApplicationForm>`. Then, I\'m conceptualizing the `contact` page as a \"Concierge Liaison\" with a form and contact details.\n\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will update `/src/index.css` to load our beautiful custom Google Fonts: **Cormorant Garamond** (for the editorial serif styling, inspired by Dior), **Inter** (for clean UI sans-serif text), and **JetBrains Mono** (for authentic-feeling registry numbers and birth dates). I will also extend Tailwind CSS v4\'s theme directly inside the stylesheet."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 815755831
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
